President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of North Dakota due to flooding from October 9 to October 26, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available to governments and nonprofit organizations for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, there will be funding for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Dana C. Reynolds has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the State and based on damage assessments. For more information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.